BOJ’s Shirakawa Says Japan’s Economic Situation Is ’Very Severe’

-- B y   K e n   M c C a l l u m
-- 
2011-10-05T02:19:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/boj-s-shirakawa-says-japan-s-economic-situation-is-very-severe-.html
Bank of Japan (8301)  Governor Masaaki
Shirakawa said he feels that the nation’s economic state and
outlook are “very severe.”  The central bank is taking “strong” monetary easing steps
to support the economy, he said in parliament in  Tokyo  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ken McCallum in Tokyo at 
